def: To determine an issue of fact, and to declare such adetermination to a court; as, the jury find for the plaintiff.Burrill.
A passage for water, such as was usually made in a sea wall, todrain water out of marshes. Burrill.
To be without, or to resign, possession of. [Obs.]
Written in, or pertaining to, hierograms; expressive of sacredwriting. Bp. Warburton.
The great river of Egypt. Nile bird. (Zoöl.) (a) The wryneck.[Prov. Eng.] (b) The crocodile bird.-- Nile goose (Zoöl.), the Egyptian goose. See Note under Goose, 2.
The state of a daughter, or the conduct becoming a daughter.
Having a lawn; characterized by a lawn or by lawns; like alawn.Musing through the lawny park. T. Warton.
Articles made of iron, as household utensils, tools, and thelike.
The day of the annunciation of the Virgin Mary, March 25. SeeAnnunciation.
